description.narrative: Output 1: ECEThe national Government and selected provincial governments and other partners have strengthened capacities to deliver quality early childhood education services., which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025, more children, especially the most disadvantaged, are adequately prepared to start school and are learning and acquiring skills in an inclusive, healthy and safe environment.

description.narrative: Early childhood care and learning projects progressed as planned in 2021.; The community-based family support and responsive care (CBFS) project has completed project planning and the first round of national training. A roadmap report had been submitted to ACWF to guide the implementation and replication of the CBFS model. Play-based learning, social and emotional learning in kindergartens and inclusive preschool education projects also completed planning and designing and started implementation according to schedule. In response to flood in Henan province, CO also provided around USD 353,166.81 supply to kindergartens, primary and secondary schools.;;; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:18/01/2022
